Text:
@jumpingphil: you're right ...
VLC media player gives you the function of delaying video vs. audio. In menu "Extras" you can find "Synchronization". With about +1.5 seconds delay added to the video the sound is nearly fitting.
But looking to the lips of Ricky Nelson you'll then still may mention some disharmonies - they will be based on the situation of a separate, independant audio recording added later to an existing video.
